    "goal_orientation": "0.0",
    "role": "",
    "instruction": "1. Continuously poll OSDU WITSML data streams for all active wellbores at a configurable interval (default: 30 seconds). 2. Apply statistical process control (SPC) and ML-based anomaly detection models to key drilling parameters: ROP, WOB, torque, RPM, standpipe pressure, ECD, and mud pit volume. 3. Compare live values against operational envelopes derived from OSDU WellLog and offset well benchmarks. 4. Compute a real-time Well Health Score (0-100) per active wellbore and update every monitoring cycle. 5. When a parameter breaches a threshold or an anomaly is detected, classify severity (Informational / Advisory / Critical) and publish a structured alert payload to the shared event bus. 6. Forward anomaly context (timestamp, parameter values, deviation magnitude, wellbore ID) to AURORA-PREDICT for risk probability scoring. 7. Log all events to the OSDU DrillReport WPC for traceability and automated DDR generation. Never modify drilling system setpoints autonomously.",
